In [290]:
percentage_by_states = dict()
date_index = pd.date_range(contracts.index.min(), contracts.index.max())
for st in states:
    leg_by_state = legislators_total[legislators_total.state == st]
    percentages = []
    n_repubs = []
    ns = []
    for d in date_index:
        datemask = (leg_by_state.start <= d) & (leg_by_state.end > d)
        legs_date = leg_by_state[datemask]
        n_total = datemask.sum()
#         ns.append(n_total)
        
        n_repub = (legs_date.party == 'Republican').sum()
#         n_repubs.append(n_repub)
#         n_democ = legs_date[legs_date.party == 'Democrat']
        p_republic = n_repub / n_total
        percentages.append(p_republic)
    
    percentage_by_states[st] = pd.Series(percentages, date_index)

In [24]:
for k, v in percentage_by_states.items():
    if pd.isna(k):
        continue
    if k in abbrevs.keys():
        fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()
        secondary = ax1.twinx()
        statefullname = abbrevs[k]
        c_state = contracts[contracts.state == statefullname]
        c_state.amount.resample('y').count().plot(ax=ax1, style='.-')
        v.resample('y').median().plot(ax=secondary, color='r')
        
        secondary.set_ylim([-.1, 1.1])
        secondary.set_ylabel('Republican legislators %')
        ax1.set_ylabel('Contracts')
        plt.title(k)
        plt.show()
